This paper is likely to belong to the cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) sub-category as it focuses on detecting insider threats in computer networks, which is a cybersecurity concern. The use of deep learning models also suggests that it could belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves unsupervised learning, which could place it in the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-category. The focus on analyzing structured data streams could also place it in the cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) sub-category. Finally, the use of neural networks suggests that it could belong to the cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) sub-category.
